sys_ui_annotation.text: General Information

type.display_value: Section header with top line

sys_ui_annotation.text: Impact Statements

type.display_value: Section header with top line

sys_ui_annotation.text: If the arrangement was suddenly discontinued because of a failure of the function/service, would it affect any of the Outcomes below?

type.display_value: Section header

sys_ui_annotation.text: 1. Continue to meet daily clearing, settlement and other time-critical obligations.

type.display_value: Section sub header with top line

sys_ui_annotation.text: 2. Monitor and manage its financial positions, including credit, liquidity and market risk positions, operational risk, prudential regulatory reporting and management accounting.

type.display_value: Section sub header with top line

sys_ui_annotation.text: 3. Make available the systems and financial data necessary for a statutory manager or the Reserve Bank to have available a range of options for managing Kiwibank, in the unlikely event that it failed. This relates to any data which a Statutory Manager might need IN ADDITION to that already covered in 1, 2 or 4.

type.display_value: Section sub header with top line

sys_ui_annotation.text: 4. Consider all customer types (retail, SME, business and institutional). Services for NZ dollar transactional, savings and credit or similar accounts, used by individuals and businesses, including Automatic Teller Machine (ATM) services

type.display_value: Section sub header with top line

sys_ui_annotation.text: 5. Any other impact on Kiwibank's operations and customers in the event the supplier is unable to deliver the required service/system, either temporarily or longer term

type.display_value: Section sub header with top line

sys_ui_annotation.text: 6. If service is a banking product not covered by basic banking, would Kiwibank be able to close out and manage wind down of it

type.display_value: Section sub header with top line

sys_ui_annotation.text: Excluded Services and Functions

type.display_value: Section header with top line

sys_ui_annotation.text: Arrangements identified as outside the scope of BS11 are listed on Kiwibank's guidance on the Exempt List and Not Outsourcing List available from the Compliance with Outsourcing Requirements BS11 OurSpace here. Any other outsourcing arrangement which is not on the Reserve Bank's Exempt List or Not Outsourcing list is therefore within scope for BS11. The Exempt List will change, so ensure that you use the latest version of the List

type.display_value: Section header

sys_ui_annotation.text: All of the function or service to be provided falls within an item on the White list, and meet all parts of the item definition

type.display_value: Section sub header with top line

sys_ui_annotation.text: If the arrangement is software falling within Exempt List items 8.2 or 9.2, also provide the Exempt List number of the related function

type.display_value: Section sub header with top line

sys_ui_annotation.text: IF your arrangement matches a Exempt List number (but not 8.1), is your arrangement directly relevant to a BS11 Outcome in the impacts list?

type.display_value: Section sub header with top line

sys_ui_annotation.text: Have you agreed with Compliance a specific interpretation for this contract which means that it does not need to be BS11 compliant? Please give a brief explanation here and attach evidence.

type.display_value: Section sub header with top line

sys_ui_annotation.text: If all answers in [Outcomes] are No but the arrangement does not match a Exempt List or Not Outsourcing description: we may be able to apply to the Reserve Bank to confirm your arrangement is outside BS11 or to add an additional function to the Exempt List. Raise this with your Operational Risk and Compliance Specialist.

type.display_value: Section sub header with top line

sys_ui_annotation.text: BS11 Conclusion

type.display_value: Section header with top line

sys_ui_annotation.text: There are additional requirements for outsourcing to related parties, or to independent third parties through a related party. Related parties are other entities in the Kiwi Group Holdings Limited group and its shareholders (e.g. NZ Post). (If in doubt, ask)

type.display_value: Section sub header with top line

sys_ui_annotation.text: If the answer to previous is Yes, Kiwibank must apply to the Reserve Bank for 'non-objection', prior to the finalisation of the outsourcing arrangement. Consult your Operational Risk and Compliance Specialist who will involve central Compliance. This is not required if the Reserve Bank has given "pre-approval" for the service/function.

type.display_value: Section sub header with top line

sys_ui_annotation.text: Will the arrangement involve or support our financial advice activities (including QFE advisers and class advice) or our derivatives issuer activities?

type.display_value: Section sub header with top line

sys_ui_annotation.text: Will the arrangement involve the supplier storing/processing or transmitting any credit card or debit card data, such as card numbers or details of transactions?

type.display_value: Section sub header with top line
